'''Adrianus G. Jacobs''' (born 1936)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://people.equilar.com/bio/adrianus-jacobs-ing-groep/salary/86892|title=Adrianus G. Jacobs - Executive Bio, Compensation History, and Contacts - Equilar Atlas|publisher=equilar.com|accessdate=20 July 2016}}</ref> is a Dutch businessman, the former chairman of [[Royal Dutch Shell]] from 2004 to 2006,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/business/3960725.stm|title=Profits rise as Shell unites board|date=28 October 2004|publisher=|accessdate=20 July 2016|via=bbc.co.uk}}</ref> and of [[ING Group]] from 1992 to 1998.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.wsj.com/articles/SB880912441409533000|title=Jacobs Is Set to Retire As ING Groep Chairman|first=Christopher|last=Rhoads|date=1 December 1997|publisher=[[Wall Street Journal]]|accessdate=20 July 2016}} {{subscription required}}</ref><ref name="nytimes">{{cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/1995/03/07/business/worldbusiness/07iht-barings_1.html|title=ING Gets Barings With Vow to Cover $1.4 Billion Loss|website=NYTimes.com|accessdate=2 August 2017}}</ref>
Jacobs has been a director of numerous companies.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/research/stocks/private/person.asp?personId=619386&privcapId=324718|title=Aad G. Jacobs: Executive Profile & Biography - Businessweek|publisher=[[bloomberg.com]]|accessdate=20 July 2016}}</ref> In 2002, Jacobs was inducted into the [[Insurance Hall of Fame]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Insurance Hall of Fame Laureate Profile|url=http://www.insurancehalloffame.org/laureateprofile.php?laureate=18|website=Insurance Hall of Fame|accessdate=8 November 2017}}</ref>
