{{Companies law}}

'''{{lang|da|Anpartsselskab}}''' ('''ApS''') is the [[Denmark|Danish]] term for a [[private limited company]]. ApS, when appended to the end of a Danish company name, is similar to [[Ltd.]] after the name of a British company. An ApS is required to have capital of at least 50,000 [[Danish krone|DKK]] (8,220 [[Euro]]s).

