{{Infobox company | name = Novadelta, S.A. | logo = Novo logotipo Delta.png | caption = | type = [[Sociedade Anónima]] | traded_as = | genre = <!-- Only used with media and publishing companies --> | fate = | predecessor = | successor = | foundation = {{Start date|1961}} | founder = Rui Nabeiro | location_city = [[Campo Maior, Portugal|Campo Maior]] | location_country = [[Portugal]] | location = | locations = | area_served = Worldwide | key_people = | industry = | products = Coffee, tea, sandwiches and iced drinks | services = | revenue = | operating_income = | net_income = | aum = <!-- Only used with financial services companies --> | assets = | equity = | owner = | num_employees = | parent = | divisions = | subsid = | homepage = {{URL|www.deltacafes.com/en}} | footnotes = | intl = }}
'''Delta Cafés''' ({{IPA-pt|dɛɫtɐ kɐfɛʃ}}) is a [[Portugal|Portuguese]] [[coffee]] [[coffee roasting|roasting]] and coffee packaging company headquartered in [[Campo Maior, Portugal|Campo Maior]], [[Alentejo]]. The company was founded in 1961 and is among the top market leaders in the [[Iberian Peninsula]]. The company belongs to [[Nabeiro Group]], the personal conglomerate of its founder Rui Nabeiro, which include interests on [[agribusiness]], [[agriculture]], [[real estate]], [[hotels]], and other services.<ref>[http://investing.businessweek.com/research/stocks/private/snapshot.asp?privcapId=29187715 Delta Cafes- Sociedade Gestora De ParticipaÇoes Sociais, S.a.], [[BusinessWeek]]</ref>
==History== Delta Cafés was founded by Rui Nabeiro in 1961 in the town of [[Campo Maior, Portugal|Campo Maior]], [[Alentejo]], in a small {{convert|50|m2|ft2}} warehouse, which could only handle two {{convert|30|kg|lb}} roasters and with the participation of only three workers.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.theceomagazine.com/business/rui-miguel-nabeiro/|title=Rui Miguel Nabeiro|date=2016-08-25|work=The CEO Magazine|access-date=2018-01-17|language=en-AU}}</ref> In 1994, the company became Portugal's market leader with a share of 42%.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.waymarking.com/waymarks/WMAYH8_Fbrica_da_Delta_Cafs_Campo_Maior_Portugal|title=Fábrica da Delta Cafés - Campo Maior, Portugal - Iconic Factories on Waymarking.com|website=www.waymarking.com|language=en|access-date=2018-01-17}}</ref> In 1998, the Nabeiro/Delta Cafés Group was restructured and gave rise to 22 companies organized into strategic areas, with turnover of approximately [[Euro|€]]160 million. In the 2000s, it become the market leader for coffee in Portugal, with a market share of 38%. It has 47,000 direct retail clients (among the largest of which is [[Sonae]], a leading Portuguese retailer) and 3,000 employees.<ref>[http://www.wbcsd.org/Plugins/DocSearch/details.asp?DocTypeId=24&ObjectId=MjQ1Ng&URLBack=%2Ftemplates%2FTemplateWBCSD5%2Flayout%2Easp%3Ftype%3Dp%26MenuId%3DODY%26CurPage%3D10%26SortOrder%3DPubDate%2520ASC Sonae: Delta Cafés socially responsible coffee (Case Study)], [[World Business Council for Sustainable Development]] (WBCSD).</ref> Also in the 2007, Delta Cafés launched its own [[espresso]] products, Delta Q, based on a proprietary system of single-serving "capsules" containing ground coffee and ''[[rooibos]]'', and specialized machines to brew [[espresso]] from the contents of the capsules in a similar way to that of [[Nestlé]]'s [[Nespresso]] brand portfolio.<ref>[https://imagensdemarca.sapo.pt/dossier/detalhes.php?id=496], Delta Q</ref>In October 2017, Delta Cafes partnered with the 'e-commerce' platform Alibaba.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.jornaleconomico.sapo.pt/noticias/delta-cafes-a-venda-no-gigante-online-alibaba-225506|title=Delta Cafés à venda no gigante online Alibaba|last=Silva|first=Nuno Miguel|date=2017-10-25|work=O Jornal Económico|access-date=2017-11-03|language=pt-PT}}</ref> In July 2018, Delta joined the international coffee association International Coffee Partners (ICP).<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://marketeer.pt/2018/07/05/delta-junta-se-a-associacao-internacional-de-cafe/|title=Delta junta-se a associação internacional de café|website=marketeer.pt|access-date=2018-07-25}}</ref>
