{{Merge|Front and back ends|date=January 2018}}
A '''front office application''' is any [[software]] that has a direct relation to customers. It provides functionality and data necessary to take orders, configure complex products and provide effective service and support to customers. It includes [[customer relationship management]] (CRM), [[sales force automation]], [[customer support]] and field service. <ref name="front office application Definition">{{cite web|title=front office application Definition|url=https://www.pcmag.com/encyclopedia/term/43516/front-office-application|publisher=PCMag|accessdate=16 November 2013}}</ref> In turn, a '''back office application''' has no such direct relation. It provides functionality for internal operations such as [[enterprise resource planning]] (ERP), [[inventory control]], [[manufacturing]] and all of the supply chain activities associated with procuring goods, services and raw materials. If an ERP system includes order entry and customer service capabilities, that system would bridge both back office and front office.<ref name="back office application Definition">{{cite web|title=back office application Definition|url=https://www.pcmag.com/encyclopedia/term/38343/back-office-application|publisher=PCMag|accessdate=16 November 2013}}</ref>
==Examples== The [[software]] enabling the [[customer]] to order a [[product (business)|product]] from a [[company]] is considered a front office [[Application software|application]]. If a [[salesperson]] is typing the order into the application, it is still considered a front office application even though the [[customer]] is not directly interacting with the [[software]].<ref name="front office application Definition">{{cite web|title=front office application Definition|url=https://www.pcmag.com/encyclopedia/term/43516/front-office-application|publisher=PCMag|accessdate=16 November 2013}}</ref>
If the [[company]] uses different [[software]] to order the product from a [[manufacturer]], it is considered a back office application.<ref name="back office application Definition">{{cite web|title=back office application Definition|url=https://www.pcmag.com/encyclopedia/term/38343/back-office-application|publisher=PCMag|accessdate=16 November 2013}}</ref>
== See also == * [[Front office]] * [[Back office]]
