'''''The Trademark Reporter''''' is a bimonthly [[peer-reviewed]] [[academic journal]] covering [[trademark law]] and related topics. It was first established in 1911<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.inta.org/Press/Pages/TMRCentennial.aspx |title=The Trademark Reporter Celebrates 100 Years of Publication |publisher=[[International Trademark Association]]}}</ref> and is published by the [[International Trademark Association]]. Articles published by the journal have been cited by different courts.<ref>[https://supreme.justia.com/cases/federal/us/505/763/case.pdf United States Supreme Court: Two Pesos v. Taco Cabana, 505 U.S. 763 (1992)]</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://scholar.google.com/scholar_case?case=4383532264167706068&hl=en&as_sdt=6&as_vis=1&oi=scholarr |title=Louis Vuitton Malletier v. Dooney & Bourke, Inc., 454 F. 3d 108 - Court of Appeals, 2nd Circuit 2006 |work=[[Google Scholar]]}}</ref><ref>[http://ttabvue.uspto.gov/ttabvue/ttabvue-91194974-OPP-109.pdf TTAB Decision: ProMark Brands Inc. and H.J. Heinz Company v. GFA Brands, Inc., 114 U.S.P.Q.2d 1232 (TTAB 2015)]</ref>

